properties.areaDesc: Motherlode; West Slope Northern Sierra Nevada
properties.headline: Winter Storm Warning issued January 16 at 3:05AM PST until January 17 at 6:00AM PST by NWS Sacramento CA
properties.description:
...Hazardous mountain travel into early Friday...

.A winter storm will bring moderate to heavy snow to the mountains
and upper foothills into Friday. Mountain travel will be very
difficult with reduced visibility, chain controls, and possible
road closures. Gusty winds may bring periods of whiteout
conditions. Plan ahead and continue to monitor the forecast.

* WHAT...Heavy snow developing. Travel will be very difficult to
impossible. Total snow accumulations of 1 to 2 feet, with
locally higher amounts, are expected.

* WHERE...Motherlode and West Slope Northern Sierra Nevada
including Interstate 80 over Donner Pass and Highway 50 over
Echo Summit.

* WHEN...6 AM today to 6 AM Friday.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Be prepared for significant reductions in
visibility at times.
properties.instruction:
A Winter Storm Warning for snow means there will be snow covered
roads and limited visibilities. Travel is not recommended while
the warning is in effect. If you must travel, keep an extra
flashlight, food and water in your vehicle in case of an
emergency.The latest road conditions for the state you are
calling from can be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER STORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 6 AM THIS MORNING TO 6 AM PST FRIDAY ABOVE 2000 FEET
